data.name: BuyNowLink.Text
data.value:
Welcome to Journal Six, your electronic knitting journal for the E6000 knitting machine. Organize your projects, stitch patterns, form programmes, and knit techniques in an easy to search database.
Journal Six is fully integrated with your E6000. Download stitch patterns and card reader techniques to your knitting machine with a standard E6000 download cable. Download charts for knitting custom forms (if your console chip set supports it.)
Sophisticated image processing techniques convert photos, scans, and original designs from a wide variety of graphics formats into high quality stitch patterns. Reduce colors. Choose special effects such as stippling or hatching. Apply custom color separations. Emblish stitch patterns with the sketchbook.
Journal Six automatically records your work as you go along. Refer to your favorite projects over and over again. Journal Six handles the organization and note taking so that you are free to be creative.

data.name: Label2.Text
data.value:
Welcome to PASSAP Pal, your electronic knitting journal for the E6000. Organize your projects, stitch patterns, form programs, and knit techniques in an easy to search database. PASSAP Pal is fully integrated with your E6000. Download stitch patterns, form programs, and even custom knit techniques to your knitting machine with a standard E6000 download cable.
PASSAP Pal automatically journalizes your work as you go along. Refer to your favorite projects over and over again. PASSAP Pal handles the organization and note taking so that you are free to be creative.
If you are ready to dive in, click on the "Projects" link on the facing page. Or, click the "Tutorial" link to learn the many functions and features of PASSAP Pal. Happy Knitting!

data.name: PCStartFormButton.ToolTip
data.value: Press this button when the E6000 console displays FORM to get ready to download this knit technique. Next, press the unlabeled key on the console followed by the zero key. The console will then display PC START. Press this button again to send this knit technique to your knitting machine.
